238. Product of Array Except Self
Given an integer array nums, return an array answer such that answer[i] is equal to the product of all the elements of nums except nums[i].
The product of any prefix or suffix of nums is guaranteed to fit in a 32-bit integer.
You must write an algorithm that runs in O(n) time and without using the division operation.

Example 1:
Input: nums = [1,2,3,4]
Output: [24,12,8,6]

Example 2:
Input: nums = [-1,1,0,-3,3]
Output: [0,0,9,0,0]
 

Constraints:
2 <= nums.length <= 105
-30 <= nums[i] <= 30
The input is generated such that answer[i] is guaranteed to fit in a 32-bit integer.
 
Follow up: Can you solve the problem in O(1) extra space complexity? (The output array does not count as extra space for space complexity analysis.)

Brute-Force Approach: By storing the total product with all elements and while storing in ans divide by the given element on respective index. 
[What to do if we are not allowed to do the division method ?]

Next Approach: By running loop for traversing element and second loop for keeping the products on ans array by eleminating the nums array element.
[Time limit Exceed for large number of array elments]

Solution:-
class Solution {
    
    public int[] productExceptSelf(int[] nums) {
        int ans[]=new int[nums.length];
       
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
            int prod=1;
            for(int j=0;j<nums.length;j++){
                if(i!=j){
                    prod *= nums[j];
                }
            }
            ans[i]=prod;
        }
        return ans;
    }
}

Next Approach: By keeping leftProduct in one array and right product in another array. Then putting the product of left and right array elemennt on ans[pos] index.

class Solution {
    public int[] productExceptSelf(int[] nums) {
     int n=nums.length;
     int leftarr[]=new int[n];
     int rightarr[]=new int[n];
     int ans[]=new int[n];
     leftarr[0]=1;
     rightarr[n-1]=1;
     
     for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
       leftarr[i]=leftarr[i-1]*nums[i-1];
     }
     for(int i=n-2;i>=0;i--){
       rightarr[i]=rightarr[i+1]*nums[i+1];
     }
     
     for(int k=0;k<ans.length;k++){
       ans[k]=leftarr[k]*rightarr[k];
     }
     return ans;
    }
}
